1. install python and make sure everything is checked
2. use the command line to cd to the directory of the
	website you want to test
3. 	# If Python version returned above is 3.X
	python -m http.server
	# If Python version returned above is 2.X
	python -m SimpleHTTPServer
4. Open the web browser and type in localhost:8000
5. You're webpage should display and async should work!

Optional: If something is already running on port: 8000
		  port 8000 is the default so you can change it
	python -m http.server 7800 (Python 3.x)
	python -m SimpleHTTPServer 7800 (Python 2.x)